The paper focuses on using deep learning methods to predict sleep quality based on wearable data, which falls under the category of machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential use of these predictive models in eHealth solutions, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) or cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). The use of actigraphy sensors for studying sleep and physical activity patterns could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
